mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;The
proposed new dwelling by reason of its siting would reduce the spaciousness
between the host dwelling and the East boundary. &amp;nbsp;This would unbalance the
symmetry and uniformity of the terraces given their rhythm and regular form. The
spaciousness between the property and the entrance to the banjo cul-de-sac is a
characteristic heritage feature of the Becontree Estate. The proposal would
result in an adverse impact on the open character of this streetscene, and
appear overly intrusive by reducing this gap and disrupting the build line between
the existing terrace and the terrace on the banjo cul-de-sac. Properties
positioned at the entrance of a banjo cul-de-sac have been dismissed at appeal
for similar reasoning, for example; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;APP/Z5060/D/21/3278270&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;
